## SYNOPSIS


  nim - Nim programming language file hook
  __%fhook-nim-exec__  
  __%fhook-nim-format__  
  __%fhook-nim-lint__  


## FILES


  __hknim.emf__ - Nim programming language hook definition  
  __nim.etf__ - Nim programming language template file
  __nim.eaf__ - Nim programming language abbreviation file

## EXTENSIONS


  __.nim__ - Nim file


## DESCRIPTION


  The __nim__ file hook provides simple hilighting of Nim files,
  folding, item listing, abbreviations and indentation support.

  __General Editing__
  
  >  On creating a new file, a new header is automatically included into
     the file. [time(2m)](time(2m)) is by default enabled, allowing the modification
     time-stamp to be maintained in the header.

  __Hilighting__
  
  >  The hilighting features allow commands, variables, logical,
     preprocessor definitions, comments, strings and characters of the
     language to be differentiated and rendered in different colors.

  __Folding and Information Hiding__
  
  >  Generic folding is enabled within the Nim files. The folds occur
     about the __proc__ keyword and an following empty line.

  > - [collapse-all(3)](collapse-all(3)) (un)folds all regions in the file, 
    - [collapse-current(3)](collapse-current(3)) (un)folds the current region. 

  __Navigation via Item List__

  >  The Nim mode offers beside folding as well support for displaying an outline
     of the functions and types of the Nim file for easy navigation using the 
     [item-list(3)](item-list(3)) command. 

  __Abbreviations__

  >  The  installation  comes with a default  abbreviation  file for Nim file
     editing which  can  be  used  by  writing  short   abbreviations like
     "_fo_" (for), "_if_", "_ei_" (elif), or "_pr_" (proc) - and then 
     pressing the key-binding  for the [expand-abbrev-handle(3)](expand-abbrev-handle(3)) command.
     The  list  of  abbreviations  can be used  interactively  in the GUI version of
     MicroEmacs using the [abbrev-list(3)](abbrev-list(3)) command.

  __Working Environment__
  
  >  [compile(3)](compile(3)) may be invoked to rebuild the source, the user is prompted
     to save any files.

  __Short Cuts__
  
  >  The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-

  >  __C-c C-c__ - Comment out the current line.  
     __C-c C-d__ - Uncomment the current line.  

  >  __f2__ - (Un)fold the current region.  
     __f3__ - (Un)fold all regions.  

  >  __f6__ - Display the item list.
     __esc f6__ - Hide the item list.

  __Executing, Formatting and Linting__
  
  > __%fhook-nim-exec__ - The command to execute the current Nim file, default
       is set to _"nim r --verbosity:0 \"%f\""_ where %f represents the file name  
  > __%fhook-nim-format__ - The command to format current Nim file, default  
       is set to _"nph %f"_ where %f represents the file name  
  > __%fhook-nim-lint__ - The command to check/lint the current Nim file, 
       default is set to _"nim c --verbosity:0 \"%f\""_ 
  
  > The setting assume that the _Nim_ compiler and the _nph_ formatter are available via the _PATH_
    environment variable. On Windows you must insert here either the complete 
    _PATH_ to the  _`nim`_ executable or add the folder where this file is to the
    _PATH_ variable.

  > These global variables should be changed if necessary usually within your _USERNAME.emf_ 
    or the _mynim.emf_ file. 

    
